## Manual Steps Still Required

If the workflow still fails after commit c909b7a, the next check is the GitHub
environment secrets. The workflow uses `environment: staging`, which means all three
secrets must be defined under Settings → Environments → staging in the repo —
not under Settings → Secrets → Actions (repo-level).

Secrets required in the staging environment:

  SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN         — personal access token from app.supabase.com/account/tokens
  SUPABASE_STAGING_DB_PASSWORD  — database password for the staging Supabase project
  SUPABASE_STAGING_PROJECT_ID   — project ref (e.g. abcdefghijklmnop) for the staging project

If the `staging` environment does not exist at all, create it first:
  1. Go to: github.com/hendrencustomhomes/hendren-platform/settings/environments
  2. Click "New environment", name it exactly: staging
  3. Add the three secrets listed above
  4. Optionally add required reviewers or deployment protection rules

If any secret is missing or empty, every ${{ secrets.* }} reference resolves to an
empty string and `supabase link --project-ref ""` will fail regardless of the
--password fix.

